@node "FAQ" "FAQ"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}Q: When will the Kąą FServ be available?@{ub}
A: Never.A Kąą Fserv will be inferiour to dedicated Fserv servers
   such as FTPd,amibot or eggdrop(best).

@{b}Q: Some loosers are trying to take over my channel how can kuang help?@{ub}
A: A lot obviously.Click on @{"this" link Protect} to read the manual of how to set
it up.

@{b}Q: What is NetHack protection?@{ub}
A: When a server rejoins after a split it may op the users
   which are on it.This can be used to take over a channel.
   If you turn on NetHack protection (/KC NHP) then every
   such action by the server will be reversed , but not conflict
   with you userlist.So,I don't recommend turning it on unless
   your friends list contains most of the ops in the channel.

@{b}Q: How can I mix Kuang Eleven with other scripts I have without
   conflict?@{ub}
A: It depends on which event the script works.If the script works
   as a public channel command you can add it to kuang11pub.amirx -
   check it out.
   If the script uses the CTCP event,you can add it as a @{"CTCP plugin." link Plugins}
   If your script uses another event,read @{"this" link Doubler}.
@{b}Q: I have many packs on my XDCC.Sometimes I get flooded off
       on XDCC LIST requests?!@{ub}
A: Use less packs.Kuang cant be flooded off with XDCC,but if you
   send stuff to the server while many xdcc lists are sent you can
   get flooded.Since version 3, Kuang uses the AmIRC feature of CTCP throttling
   via the QUEUERAW command.This should prevent flooding by delaying lines sent to
   the server.If THAT doesn't work, you should send mail to Oliver Wagner about it.
@{b}Q: I want AutoOps/NetHack/MassDeop Protection on @{i}this@{ui} channel but I don't
   want it on @{i}that@{ui} channel.@{ub}
A: You cant toggle protection/automodes specifically per channel,as this will
   make the events handler too complex and slow.However,you can make Kuang work in
   specific channels using the AutoChannels interface via the GUI or the
   /KC ACHAN command.Normally its set to ALL but by setting the AutoChannels list
   to the channels you want Kuang to work in,you can save yourself anger of
   unfriendly ops,if you have,for instance,deopped a bunch of ops during
   NetHack :)

@{b}Q: Have you become a PC lamuh?@{ub}
A: Yes.I am now a student in the university and I want to work as a programmer.
   In my country,there is no demand for Amiga programmers :(
@endnode
@node Doubler "Using Other Scripts"
@toc MAIN
You can use other scripts in the JOIN/MODE etc. events by using the included
doubler.amirx script.This script will launch both kuang's events handler
and other scripts you specify.To do this :
1. Edit doubler.amirx and put the name of the script there.
2. Edit your config.Add an entry as :

   copyscripts [script1.amirx] <script2.amirx> ...

   Example :

   copyscripts doubler.amirx

   The scripts MUST be in the Rexx directory , otherwise Kąą will not init.
   The scripts will be placed in T: assign and deleted from there in shutdown.

3. Change your AmIRC settings/Events @{b}where required @{ub} to execute doubler.amirx
   instead of kuang11.amirx.The line should read :
   ram:doubler.amirx %p

That's it.anything else is upto you and the other script :)
@endnode
